description: Britains Lost Masterpieces: Collection 1 History Documentary hosted by Bendor Grosvenor and Jacky Klein and Emma Dabiri, published by BBC in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/d/d8/Britains-Lost-Masterpieces-Collection-1-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Britain's Lost Masterpieces: Collection 1 Historian and art dealer Dr Bendor Grosvenor, art historian Jacky Klein and Emma Dabiri celebrate the UK's local art treasures as they track down lost and hidden paintings from local museums and galleries. This Collection is made up of 3 episodes from Series 1, 4 episodes from Series 2 6) Carmarthenshire Carmarthenshire County Museum is a slice of history in itself. The building that houses it has been in continuous use since the 13th century. Once a bishop's palace, it was where the Bible was first translated into Welsh. But could it also be home to some mysterious cases of mistaken identity and two lost paintings from the time of Charles II?
